				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok,here's the deal on the 'Monk's Life':<BR>
  A monk is basically a warrior that uses his hands,and is able to heal himself,fake death,and sneak.These are very useful.<BR>
   Level 1:You can hunt black and yellow things easily.Go for the black though,just for level 1,to get your skill up.You want to put all your points,but 1,in Mend.Keep one for kick.<BR>
 Level 2:Now move on to yellow things.I did this and i even solo'ed a red bear that my level 5 mage and her pet had trouble with.I started scoring hits with my hands for 8-9 damage and 6-8 for kicks.(don't get a weapon)<BR>
Level 3:Now,since you put ALL your points into mnd,it might start to work a little bit of the time.Go get some black,yellow,and red things definatly.Monks,,by far,the easiest to level up  to about 15.<BR>
Level 4+:Now you are landing better hits and should be grouping a bit more.Be sure to PUT ALL POINTS into mend.This will save your life.I can mend while I fight.I do this if i get into trouble #=o) <BR>
Level 8:Now you are grouping more,and Are starting to ue you money for buying Wu's Fighting equipment.If you are not doing thios, start now!You need mesh and Wu's fighting armor,It adds agility,VERY USEFUL!!Get sta+ and STR+ jewelery.(Jagged Bands,Golden star amulet,ect.) <BR>
Level 10-15:Now you have good armor,and you start saving your points for Feign Death.This is the ability to pretend you are dead,making mobs leave you alone and leave.If you are near death this is very useful.Remember,all this time you were also Improving your Bind Wound skill.Monks:this SAVES YOUR LIFE!!!!!!!<BR>
Level 16:Not much to do here, except now you are going into dungeons, such as Befallen,Blackburrow,hunting at the Aviak Village,Camping higher stuff(Gnolls in Lake rathe are good)ect. And you are on the edge of your seat for lvl 17!!!<BR>
Level 17: Ahhh,level 17! Feign Death!!The moment you monks all are waiting for!Well,its here.And you put all your points into it!Ahh-hahaha!<BR>
Level 18-19:You are definatly either in Lake Rathe with the Gnolls,Aviak Village,or hunting in Nk,Sk,or Wk.This is the life of a monk.Always traveling.<BR>
Level 20: Surname!What everyone waits for. Also time to save up for the flying kick(Razor tail thingy,not sure what called,if Iksar)Dragon punch,ect. All the special move.I have seen a level 36 monk beat a level 51 Ogre warrior.Pretty amazing,with the help of these new added on skills<BR>
Level 21+: This is dungeon(paw is good) time.And time to go off on your own.I think you got the idea,so ask me if you need any more help<BR>
<BR>
