			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok just wanted to let you know i was a iksar and hman monk. human monk to lvl 5 took me all of 2 hours.  Iksar took me all of 2 hours.  Being able to see well that really doesnt matter b/c there are planty of things yo cpould be doin besides fightin, even so if you do carry a light source keep it in an empty inventory slot it still works.<BR>
<BR>
Also about lvling these first 5 lvls determine a lot if you can do it fast you already beat the first third of your character.  these are the hardest lvls in the game b/c your poor you attack for next to nothin and it takes forever to kill a bloody snake.  <BR>
<BR>
Also one other thing to consider if you like soloing then be an iksar b/c thats all your really gonna be doin for awhile cuz not many ppl play the lizards.  <BR>
<BR>
Humans have another great advantage snd that is it is a short boat ride to the greatest low lvl zone. Incase you dont know which zone that is it is Greater Faydark.  It has quest items from all 3 of its surrounding cities,  another zone that can be good for teens and twenties when done right, and easy access to just about nething you need.  Excpet your guild which bites the hairy bird but youll get over that fact.<BR>
<BR>
NEWays thats my opinion on the subject so take it or leave it.<BR>
<BR>
I have too many monks to name them all but currently using Gezbed of the Fire Breathers <BR>
Xev Server
