	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In reply to this last post, I'd like to say a thing or two.  The last post mentioned that humans were better stat wise.  But, if you look at the starting stats, humans are only stronger in STR, STA and CHA, one of which monks don't really need.  To turn the tables, Iksar have higher starting AGI and DEX, which are both used like STR and STA.  A human is only 5 AP points higher than iksar in STR/STA, but an iksar is 15 AP points higher in AGI and 10 AP points in DEX.  And night vision doesnt matter?  One of the things I hated the most while playing as a human monk was not seeing a damn thing.  As i see it, I'd rather keep a spot on my persona saved for a stat booster rather than a light source. <BR>
<BR>
I do admit that after about lvl 20, regen doesn't matter, but that still leaves 20 lvls where it does.  Swimming isnt a big thing for a monk, but can be a convienence if running.  I don't think anyone can argue with a naturally high AC, though, that helps anyone.  All and All, statistically, I believe Iksars are higher, but I believe in Role-playing, and if you feel like a human monk, go for it.  I know a lot of people who have problems running around as an upright lizard...<BR>
<BR>
Althur the Swift
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
